summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on Western Sahara, reaffirms its commitment to a just, lasting and mutually acceptable political solution for self-determination.

It calls on parties and regional States to cooperate with the UN to end the impasse.

The Council:

1. Reaffirms need for full respect of military agreements with MINURSO on ceasefire;
2. Calls on Member States to consider voluntary contributions for confidence-building measures, particularly family unification visits;
3. Requests the Secretary-General to report on the situation before the end of the mandate period;
4. Requests the Secretary-General to ensure MINURSO complies with the UN's zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse;
5. Extends MINURSO's mandate until 31 October 2006;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
